# IMP-0003

# Internal Event Bus (IEB)

Status: Draft

Version: 0.1

Depends on:

* RFC-0020 Hypervisor Architecture
* IMP-0002 Embedded Service Architecture
* ADR-0001 Service Ownership Principle

---

# 1. Purpose

The Internal Event Bus (IEB) provides asynchronous communication between Hypervisor services.

The Event Bus exists entirely within a single Hypervisor process.

It is not a network protocol.

It is not a message broker.

---

# 2. Design Goals

The Event Bus SHALL:

* eliminate direct coupling between services;
* support synchronous and asynchronous subscribers;
* provide deterministic event ordering;
* avoid cyclic dependencies;
* remain lightweight.

---

# 3. Event Model

Every Event consists of:

```yaml id="5o2bcm"
event:

  event_id:

  event_type:

  timestamp:

  source:

  payload:

  correlation_id:

  sequence:
```

---

# 4. Event Ownership

Every Event SHALL have exactly one Publisher.

An Event MAY have zero or more Subscribers.

Subscribers SHALL NOT modify Event contents.

Events are immutable.

